snippet.textDisplay: Had this whole album on repeat since it came out. Mac Millers music has gotten me through many dark days, and it feels like he died right when his true genius was only beginning to shine. He could have had so many brighter days, continued to grow so much as an artist and lived such an incredible life, made so much more music that would have touched so many peoples lives. Someone said it feels like he came down from heaven to give us this album and I feel that statement. I wish someone could have helped you like you helped us Mac, all I can really do is say thank you for the priceless body of work you left us, I know your in a better place but damn do we all miss you. RIP Malcom, your life may have been short but you made it to legendary status which most never do in a whole lifetime.

snippet.textDisplay: Everytime I hear a Mac Miller song my heart wrenches for the loss of such a talented young person. I read comments about how he altered and continues to alter lives and I nearly weep at the grief expunged. I want to shout Joplin, Hendrix, Cobain, Tupac, Biggie, Chester, Mac Miller, why God? why? Then I am reminded that not all the flowers in a garden stay. Sometimes you pick the most beautiful to take inside. snippet.textDisplay: Macs music got me through my suicide attempts back in 2015. I used to blast weekend while I drank myself into Oblivion. After those attempts didn't succeed (obviously) I took it as a sign that i just wasn't meant to go out that way. His music guided me through the lowest lows of my life, and my heart still aches knowing he's gone. I'm not sure if im in denial or what but I still kind of refuse to believe it.
